  "notes": "Iban (Jaku Iban) of Sarawak, written in the Latin script with Malay-style spelling conventions: ⟨ny⟩=/ɲ/, ⟨ng⟩=/ŋ/, ⟨c⟩=/tʃ/, ⟨j⟩=/dʒ/, ⟨y⟩=/j/. Six vowels /i e ə a o u/, with ⟨e⟩ writing both /e/ and /ə/. Vowels are nasalised after a nasal consonant; word-final ⟨k⟩ is commonly a glottal stop. The indigenous Dunging script exists but is not in general use and is not covered here.",
